@startuml runtime-collaboration
title Advanced Agent — Runtime Collaboration (messages during one turn)

skinparam linetype ortho
hide empty members

legend left
  Arrows are messages sent at runtime (not ownership).
  The context is immutable: phases return a *new* context.
endlegend

class Session
class AgentLoop
class Navigator
class "AgentExecutionContext" as Context
class ReasonPhase
class ActionPhase
class ObservationPhase
interface ChatModel
class ToolExecutor
interface Approver
interface ToolInterface
class Controller
class EventBus
class ProgressView
interface Renderer

' driving the loop
Session --> AgentLoop : run(context)
AgentLoop --> ReasonPhase : run(context)
AgentLoop --> ActionPhase : run(context)
AgentLoop --> ObservationPhase : run(context)
AgentLoop --> Navigator : next(phase, outcome)
note right of Navigator
  returns Continue(nextPhase)
  or Halt (end the run)
end note

' what each phase does
ReasonPhase --> ChatModel : complete(conversation, tools)
ReasonPhase --> Context : with_assistant(completion)
ActionPhase --> ToolExecutor : execute(toolCall)
ActionPhase --> Context : with_tool_results(results)
ObservationPhase --> Context : observed()
ObservationPhase --> Controller : permit(context)

' tool execution chokepoint
ToolExecutor --> Approver : review(request, mutating)
ToolExecutor --> ToolInterface : invoke(request)

' observability flows one way, off the bus
ReasonPhase ..> EventBus : publish(ModelCalled)
ToolExecutor ..> EventBus : publish(ToolInvoked / ToolObserved)
ObservationPhase ..> EventBus : publish(CycleCompleted / GuardTripped)
AgentLoop ..> EventBus : publish(PhaseStarted / LoopStopped)
EventBus ..> ProgressView : handle(event)
ProgressView ..> Renderer : show(text)

@enduml
